      "content": "The argument for humanitarian asylum is morally defensible, as it prioritizes the protection of vulnerable lives and upholds the principles of human rights and international law. The notion that a country has a duty to protect its own borders at all costs is a flawed argument, as it disregards the inherent dignity and worth of individuals fleeing persecution, violence, or poverty. By prioritizing asylum seekers' safety and well-being, we uphold the moral imperative to protect the most vulnerable members of society.",
